03 Jul 2011 09:36






Maybe it's my professional bias but come on, man Scientific improbability of a force having infinite effective range aside, this would imply the knife being able to, for example, prevent aliens from a far-away planet from destroying Earth. However cool that may be (who knows, maybe this SCP is the only reason why we are still around!), this would be way  over the top.

Then again, what the hell. Upvoted. I have suspended my disbelief for worse, the issue of range has provided some good narrativium and the whole thing is excellent.

One question: is  case mentioned in the main text related to the separately-reported incident? Because as far as I can tell, the descriptions are inconsistent if so and the former is not the only such incident if not.







