Object Class


25 Feb 2012 20:54






I really liked the concept and the simple, yet horrifying nature of 668. The text is well-written and having narratives of incidents where the item was involved amongst civilians really added to the immersion.

I have one objection though. This shouldn't be classified as Euclid, even though it's an extremely dangerous item, it only is so at the hands of a human or humanoid being bearing violent will towards others. Also, considering how well know are its properties (except for range of effect), it fails the locked box test. That being said, SCP-668 should be classified as Safe (as long as access is strictly controlled).







